        "title": "See also"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The sine is one of the fundamental functions of trigonometry (the\nmathematical study of triangles).  Consider a circle of radius 1\ncentered on the origin.  A ray comes in from the "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "+x"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " axis, makes\nan angle at the origin (measured counter-clockwise from that axis), and\ndeparts from the origin.  The "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "y"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " coordinate of the outgoing\nray's intersection with the unit circle is the sine of that angle.  It\nranges from -1 for "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "x=3\\pi / 2"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " to +1 for "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "\\pi / 2."
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "  The\nfunction has zeroes where the angle is a multiple of "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "\\pi"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ".\nSines of angles between "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "\\pi"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " and "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "2\\pi"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " are negative.\nThe numerous properties of the sine and related functions are included\nin any standard trigonometry text."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "import whest as we"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Print sine of one angle:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "we.sin(we.pi/2.)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "1.0"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Print sines of an array of angles given in degrees:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "we.sin(we.array((0., 30., 45., 60., 90.)) * we.pi / 180. )"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([ 0.        ,  0.5       ,  0.70710678,  0.8660254 ,  1.        ])"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Plot the sine function:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "import matplotlib.pylab as plt"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "x = we.linspace(-we.pi, we.pi, 201)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "plt.plot(x, we.sin(x))"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "plt.xlabel('Angle [rad]')"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "plt.ylabel('sin(x)')"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "plt.axis('tight')"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "plt.show()"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          }
        ],
